<title type="html"><![CDATA[7/12 (Thur.) Meditation &amp; Yoga/ 10 Ways to have a better conversation (Host: Way)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=186&amp;p=200#p200"><![CDATA[
It’s my honor to be host this Thursday 7/12. Many topics discussed in our club before are more focused on News/knowledge/Emotion/Philosophy/habit etc which really enrich our life and broaden our view and lead us toward healthier direction. Today, I choose softer topic “Meditation &amp; Yoga” which make us healthy mentally and physically according to my experience. Let’s discuss this soft topic in session one. Session 2, let’s discuss 10 ways to have a better conversation. Listening to Ted speech is my recommended way to improve your English listening skill. Keep going!<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session I:  Meditation &amp; Yoga</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Meditation can change Brain?</span><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W6WvLU5-Cu0&amp;app=desktop" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W6WvLU5-Cu0&amp;app=desktop</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">What are the Benefits of Yoga?</span><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CU3HuPNsyG4" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CU3HuPNsyG4</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Questions:</span><br />1.How much do you know about “Meditation”? Does Meditation really change our brain as Ted mentioned?<br />2.Can Meditation make our mind calm? Any experience do you have that you can share?<br />3.How much do you know about Yoga?<br />4.Have you played yoga before? What’s benefits yoga bring to you?<br />5.What kind of Yoga have you played? What kind of posture do you think is great?<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session II: 10 Ways to have a better conversation</span><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R1vskiVDwl4" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R1vskiVDwl4</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Questions:</span><br />1.What do you think “effective communication” means to you? Is that important in our daily life?<br />2.Do you face any conversation problems in your communication with others? How do you overcome these problems?<br />3.Do you have other recommended ways to improve communication quality besides these tips mentioned in “TED”? Or which point do you agree most in the speech?<br />4.Do you think current communication between people become better or worse after new technology is invented?<br />5.Do you have any story about misunderstanding in your past by poor conversation?  No matter what language spoken is, share with us.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Agenda</span><br />7:00-7:25 Greetings and free talk<br />7:25-7:30 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />(Session I)<br />7:30 ~ 8:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />8:10 ~ 8:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />8:25 ~ 8:30pm Regrouping<br />(Session II)<br />8:30 ~9:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />9:10 ~9:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />9:25 ~9:30pm Concluding remarks/feedback from newcomers<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">The meeting place of Thursday:</span><br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第一區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=827">Jason Tang</a> — Mon Jul 09, 2018 9:57 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
